<define-tag intro>
One of the conference's main goals is explain Linux to the world, especially to
IT/Engineering managers and to the people who make purchasing decisions within
companies. People need to learn that Open Source software and Linux are prudent
choices. Here are some of the reasons why. 
<UL>
	<LI>The entire Internet relies on Open Source software to function. 
	<LI>Nearly all ISPs use Open Source software. 
	<LI>More than 8 million people use Linux within their homes and offices. 
	<LI>More than 50% of ISPs run Linux or some other open source, Unix-compatible operating system. 
	<LI>Many open source programs are superior to their commercial counterparts. 
	<LI>Linux is being used within many companies now - though managers may not be aware of it. 
</UL>
</define-tag>

<define-tag involve>
	At the moment, Debian is uninvolved.
</define-tag>

